    <h1>Infrastructure Requirements</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p><style>[data-colorid=3Dn56bpax67q]{color:#212121} html[data-colo=
r-mode=3Ddark] [data-colorid=3Dn56bpax67q]{color:#dedede}</style>The follow=
ing infrastructure is required&nbsp;<strong>per asset</strong>&nbsp;<strong=
>per year.&nbsp;</strong></p>
<h1 id=3D"InfrastructureRequirements-Storage">Storage</h1>
<h2 id=3D"InfrastructureRequirements-LiveDatabase">Live Database</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"relative-table wrapped confluenceTable" style=3D"width: 43.=
6378%;">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 55.618%;">
<col style=3D"width: 44.382%;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Description</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Relative Size</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Sensor data in AssetPropertyValue</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">3GB / year, asset</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Postprocessor data in AssetPropert=
yValue</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">5% of Sensor Data</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Other tables</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">5% of Sensor Data</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p class=3D"auto-cursor-target">Total live DB size increase per asset per y=
ear: 3.3GB</p>
<h2 id=3D"InfrastructureRequirements-DatabaseBackup">Database Backup</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"relative-table wrapped confluenceTable" style=3D"width: 67.=
4551%;">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 56.9007%;">
<col>
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTh">Description</th>
<th colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTh">Relative Size</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Differential Backups</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">5% of Database Size</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Full backups (2 weekly, 1 after 1 month)</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">3*120% of Database Size</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>Total backup size increase per asset per year: 12GB</p>
<h2 id=3D"InfrastructureRequirements-FileStorage">File Storage</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"relative-table wrapped confluenceTable" style=3D"width: 24.=
8139%;">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 50.1672%;">
<col style=3D"width: 49.8328%;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Description</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Size</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Archived file storage</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">600MB</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>An asset requires approximately 600MB of storage to keep a copy of the r=
aw files that were sent by it.&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"InfrastructureRequirements-ApplicationLogging">Application Loggin=
g</h2>
<p>50MB / year, asset</p>
<h2 id=3D"InfrastructureRequirements-Total">Total</h2>
<p>3GB + 3GB * 0.05 + 3GB * 3 * 1.2 + 0.6GB + 0.05GB =3D<strong>&nbsp;<span=
 data-colorid=3D"n56bpax67q">14.6 GB / asset, year</span></strong></p>
<p>Meaning that to support 150 devices, we will need approximately 2.2TB pe=
r year in storage. Leaving some margin for overhead (manual backups when ne=
eded, multiple environments, ...), assume 2.5TB. Assuming the number of dev=
ices stays constant at 150, storage requirements are as follows:</p>
<p>Year 1: 2.5TB<br>Year 2: 5TB<br>Year 3: 7.5TB<br>Year 4: 10TB&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"InfrastructureRequirements-CalculationDetails">Calculation Detail=
s</h2>
<p>Calculations were made based on the data from the AGV's. The average dat=
a output over all AGV's was used. One year of data was analysed and compare=
d to the total size of the relevant tables to determine which percentage of=
 the data was caused by this asset.&nbsp;</p>
<h1 id=3D"InfrastructureRequirements-Bandwidth">Bandwidth</h1>
<p>The bandwidth requirements are rather limited. Assuming the same 600MB o=
f transferred data per asset per year, 150 assets would require approximate=
ly 90GB per year, or 7.5GB per month. Some extra bandwidth should be reserv=
ed for the website, as well as users downloading large files from the websi=
te. Modern subscriptions will allow these amounts without issue.&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"InfrastructureRequirements-Remarks">Remarks</h2>
<p>The estimate given is for a single environment. Generally, a copy of the=
 production environment is used as a testing/staging/development environmen=
t. Another copy of the database would add substantial space requirements to=
 the estimate above.&nbsp;</p>
    </div>
